@node "4"


     Before launching CleverViewer, you need to correctly set some tooltypes.
There are only two, so that's no big deal:

     - VIEWERNAME="Viewername"
     This one is the most important, to view the pics correctly. You need to
type the viewer's command as it is exactly written.

     For example, this is correct: VIEWERNAME=FastView
if your viewer is named "FastView"

     These are incorrect, though: VIEWERNAME=fastview
                                  VIEWERNAME=FASTVIEW
                                  VIEWERNAME= FastView     (notice the space!)

     - FPC=#FilesPerCommand
     You can't type a command that's too long or the viewer will return
something like "Error: command's too long!". In this case, if you use
CleverViewer, you won't even get an error message, just nothing is displayed! 
     FPC limits the number of files per command. So if FPC is set to 32 and you
have 50 files, CleverViewer will write two commands in the script to split the
list of files. 
     FPC depends on many things: the number of files, the number of active
tooltypes, etc... 
     Just try a low setting, like 16, then try something a little higher. If
pictures aren't showed anymore, then lower it again. 
     A value of 1 means that each picture is loaded by one command. That makes a
larger script file, and also you won't take advantage of the background loading
used by fastview (the next pictures are loaded while you watch the first ones!). 


     Now about the VIEWER's tooltypes.
     These will work only if the tooltype corresponds to the CLI argument. For
example the DITHER tooltype in fastview will work because when you run fastview
from CLI, the command you use to get dithering is "fastview DITHER". If your
viewer is well programmed, then this shouldn't be a problem as the tooltypes
will correspond to the CLI options. 
     Notice that the tooltypes between () will not be used. If you take a look
at the CV.temp script you'll see they don't appear in the command line. 


@endnode


@node "5"


     Here are some important notes that might solve many problems:

     - Both CleverViewer and your viewer program must be in the same directory,
the one which contains the pictures to view. 
     
     - CleverViewer uses the helvetica 11 font. Be sure it's installed. 
     
     - CleverViewer uses Icon.library . Please notice that it won't recognize
Icon.Library or icon.library , neither IcOn.LiBrArY !!! Be sure it's spelled
right in your Libs drawer. 

     - CleverViewer reads ALL the files of the directory. This means it'll read
the .info of your pics, the CleverViewer program and the FastView program. These
will be written in the CV.temp script and sent to the viewer, which will
normally just skip anything you can't view. I'm still working on a way to skip
non IFF files, but this would mean skipping jpeg, png, gif,... too!
     So you might want to get rid of the useless files, like the .info files.
But NOT THE FASTVIEW AND CLEVERVIEWER .info files !!! You need those! 


@endnode


